Sentencas: The operating properties of solid oxide fuel cells using Ni/scandia-stabilized zirconia (Ni-ScSZ) anodes under internal reforming conditions are investigated.
Titulo: Carbon deposition behaviour on Ni-ScSZ anodes for internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A single-cell achieved a maximum power density of 0.64W cm(-2) at 900degreesC in 97%CH4/3%H2O mixture fuel.
Titulo: Carbon deposition behaviour on Ni-ScSZ anodes for internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell voltage during the power generation at 0.5 A cm(-2) is stable in 97%CH4/3%H2O mixture fuel at 900degreesC for at least 150h.
Titulo: Carbon deposition behaviour on Ni-ScSZ anodes for internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By contrast, degradation of anode performance and carbon deposition are found at 800 degreesC under the same conditions.
Titulo: Carbon deposition behaviour on Ni-ScSZ anodes for internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results suggest that carbon deposition is hindered more effectively at higher temperature under operation at high current density.
Titulo: Carbon deposition behaviour on Ni-ScSZ anodes for internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells
